messages.text: Ada, where r u? I think I have something for u.
Yeah, I stole it out of his Mustang.
Along with his spare car keys.
But there’s a lot of shit on his phone about u from his dad.
And u were right about the other shit, too.
Sgt Delaney’s plan to use this thing against the Middle East and China and Russia for some kind of ethnic cleansing…
Christian must have gotten a new phone and logged it into his iMessage account.
But I’m still getting the thread on the phone I stole.
He was just texting with GI Joe.
Sgt Delaney intends to kill u if you go there.
Christian is trying to convince him otherwise, but…who knows.
I’m at the JRB base in Fort Worth.
but a huge area has been fenced off…
Some kind of pre-fab steel wall.
WTF? Do they just have shit like that lying around?
Got me. But it’s keeping the infected out.
mingling with the folks on the outside.
Even when they’re dormant these things are afraid of me…
I see it in their eyes.
These aren’t the things we see in the movies, Em.
I’ll take ur word on that.
Anything on that phone explaining WHY I'm immune to this thing?
Swell. Can you send me that shit?
Christian will know if I do.
That’s okay..if I have my way…
you’ll never see him alive again.
So ur dumping him for good, then? ☺
do you know someone named Adam?
I got some weird texts from him a couple of days ago…
he was texting Christian about some guy named Uncle Noah?
do you think Christian knows him??
I’m not sure…he seemed really afraid, though
he sounded like he wanted Christian’s help
I didn’t want him to know I had Christian’s phone
anyway, there’s no time for this right now
I have a life to save
do you think there’s enough proof on Christian’s phone to clear your dad?
So u still intend to break Woody out?
Normally, yes…but I did something really stupid.
Christian told me he was going to try and find u…
So while he was getting ready…
I hid in the trunk of his car.
I thought u could use my help. So I’m on my way to u.
No. I have a better idea.
How were you planning on getting inside?
To be honest, I hadn’t figured it out yet.
How about through the front gate?
Good. Then what can you tell me about where u r?
Well…the steel wall has to be a mile around.
Looks like there’s only one way in and out…
A front gate where the main road runs into it.
My guess is they’re holding dad somewhere inside.
Christian arrives with me in the trunk…
Slip out of here…open the gate…and let you in.
Sgt Delaney and his people will be busy fighting them…
then u scare off the dreamy-eyed zombies…
So we can steal Christian’s car and get the fuck out of Dodge.
Too many things that can go wrong.
What if someone tries to stop us?
U shoot them. Wouldn’t be ur first time. :P
You really emoji-ing me right now?
Well I’m not shooting American soldiers for doing their job.
And I’m certainly not unleashing the infected on them.
Sgt. Delaney told Christian that only their people are at the base.
Yeah…everyone inside those walls is a traitor…
and a conspirator against ur dad.
Still…I’m not comfortable with the risks to you.
Well…I’m already in the trunk so…its not really up to u.
Fine…but I don’t know what these things will do if you’re with me…
So you have to get right back in the trunk.
Cutting it a bit close, wasn’t he?
You hit a lot of dreamy-eyed someones.
There are a few Humvees and a helicopter.
But not a lot of cover either.
I don’t know about this, Em.
Pressure washer. They’re sanitizing Christian’s car.
Jesus. I never thought of that.
LOL. Sgt Delaney is yelling at Christian
He’s giving him the layout of this place…
The building closest to the gate is an armory and com-center.
The smaller hangar is a barracks and mess hall.
That’s where they fall back to if things go to shit.
Not sure. But G.I. Joe told Christian to stay the fuck away from it.
Cool. That’s where my dad is.
So they’re gonna move Christian’s car back outside the walls.
Holy Christ. Was that you screaming?
Yeah, I just heard a collective, “Fuck that shit.”
right by the entrance until morning.
I’ll be able to unlock the gate and get right back in the car.
And Em, I want you right back in that car. Got it?
Trust me…my legs are so cramped right now, it’s all I’ve got in me.
But I’m sure these things will do their part.
The rest is up to me.
OK.  C U in a few hours.
